{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id053344f6-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1401"},"text":"§ 1401.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Miscellaneous","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"When used in this subtitle or in part I of subtitle II—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id053344f7-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Vessel","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The word “vessel” includes every description of water craft or other contrivance used, or capable of being used, as a means of transportation in water, but does not include aircraft.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id053344f8-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Vehicle","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The word “vehicle” includes every description of carriage or other contrivance used, or capable of being used, as a means of transportation on land, but does not include aircraft.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id053344f9-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Merchandise","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The word “merchandise” means goods, wares, and chattels of every description, and includes merchandise the importation of which is prohibited, and monetary instruments as defined in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s5312"},"text":"section 5312 of title 31","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id053344fa-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Person","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The word “person” includes partnerships, associations, and corporations.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id053344fb-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Master","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The word “master” means the person having the command of the vessel.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id053344fc-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Day","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The word “day” means the time from eight o’clock antemeridian to five o’clock postmeridian.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id053344fd-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/g"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"g"},"text":"(g)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Night","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The word “night” means the time from five o’clock postmeridian to eight o’clock antemeridian.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id053344fe-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/h"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"h"},"text":"(h)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" United States","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “United States” includes all Territories and possessions of the United States except the Virgin Islands, American Samoa, Wake Island, Midway Islands, Kingman Reef, Johnston Island, and the island of Guam.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id053344ff-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Officer of the customs; customs officer","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The terms “officer of the customs” and “customs officer” mean any officer of the United States Customs Service of the Treasury Department (also hereinafter referred to as the “Customs Service”) or any commissioned, warrant, or petty officer of the Coast Guard, or any agent or other person, including foreign law enforcement officers, authorized by law or designated by the Secretary of the Treasury to perform any duties of an officer of the Customs Service.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id05334500-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/j"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"j"},"text":"(j)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Customs waters","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “customs waters” means, in the case of a foreign vessel subject to a treaty or other arrangement between a foreign government and the United States enabling or permitting the authorities of the United States to board, examine, search, seize, or otherwise to enforce upon such vessel upon the high seas the laws of the United States, the waters within such distance of the coast of the United States as the said authorities are or may be so enabled or permitted by such treaty or arrangement and, in the case of every other vessel, the waters within four leagues of the coast of the United States.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id05334501-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/k"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"k"},"text":"(k)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Hovering vessel","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The term “hovering vessel” means—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id05334502-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/k/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any vessel which is found or kept off the coast of the United States within or without the customs waters, if, from the history, conduct, character, or location of the vessel, it is reasonable to believe that such vessel is being used or may be used to introduce or promote or facilitate the introduction or attempted introduction of merchandise into the United States in violation of the laws of the United States; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id05334503-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/k/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any vessel which has visited a vessel described in paragraph (1).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id05334504-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/l"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"l"},"text":"(l)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Secretary","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of the Treasury or his delegate.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id05334505-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/m"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"m"},"text":"(m)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Controlled substance","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The term “controlled substance” has the meaning given that term in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s802/6"},"text":"section 802(6) of title 21","children":[],"tail":". For purposes of this chapter, a controlled substance shall be treated as merchandise the importation of which into the United States is prohibited, unless the importation is authorized under—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id05334506-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/m/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" an appropriate license or permit; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id05334507-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/m/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the Controlled Substances Import and Export Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s951"},"text":"21 U.S.C. 951","children":[],"tail":" et seq.]."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id05334508-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/n"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"n"},"text":"(n)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Electronic transmission","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “electronic transmission” means the transfer of data or information through an authorized electronic data interchange system consisting of, but not limited to, computer modems and computer networks.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id05334509-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/o"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"o"},"text":"(o)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Electronic entry","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The term “electronic entry” means the electronic transmission to the Customs Service of—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id0533450a-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/o/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" entry information required for the entry of merchandise, and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id0533450b-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/o/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" entry summary information required for the classification and appraisement of the merchandise, the verification of statistical information, and the determination of compliance with applicable law.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id0533450c-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/p"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"p"},"text":"(p)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Electronic data interchange system","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “electronic data interchange system” means any established mechanism approved by the Commissioner of U.S. Customs and Border Protection through which information can be transferred electronically.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id0533450d-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/q"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"q"},"text":"(q)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" National Customs Automation Program","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “National Customs Automation Program” means the program established under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1411"},"text":"section 1411 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id0533450e-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/r"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"r"},"text":"(r)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Import activity summary statement","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “import activity summary statement” refers to data or information transmitted electronically to the Customs Service, in accordance with such regulations as the Secretary prescribes, at the end of a specified period of time which enables the Customs Service to assess properly the duties, taxes and fees on merchandise imported during that period, collect accurate statistics and determine whether any other applicable requirement of law (other than a requirement relating to release from customs custody) is met.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id0533450f-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/s"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"s"},"text":"(s)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Reconciliation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “reconciliation” means an electronic process, initiated at the request of an importer, under which the elements of an entry (other than those elements related to the admissibility of the merchandise) that are undetermined at the time the importer files or transmits the documentation or information required by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1484/a/1/B"},"text":"section 1484(a)(1)(B) of this title","children":[],"tail":", or the import activity summary statement, are provided to the Customs Service at a later time. A reconciliation is treated as an entry for purposes of liquidation, reliquidation, recordkeeping, and protest."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id05334510-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/t"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"t"},"text":"(t)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Reconfigured entry","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “reconfigured entry” means an entry filed on an import activity summary statement which substitutes for all or part of 1 or more entries filed under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1484/a/1/A"},"text":"section 1484(a)(1)(A) of this title","children":[],"tail":" or filed on a reconciliation entry that aggregates the entry elements to be reconciled under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1484/b"},"text":"section 1484(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":" for purposes of liquidation, reliquidation, or protest."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id05334511-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1930-06-17/ch497"},"text":"June 17, 1930, ch. 497","children":[],"tail":", title IV, § 401, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/46/708"},"text":"46 Stat. 708","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-05/ch438"},"text":"Aug. 5, 1935, ch. 438","children":[],"tail":", title II, § 201, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/521"},"text":"49 Stat. 521","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1938-06-25/ch679/s2"},"text":"June 25, 1938, ch. 679, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/1077"},"text":"52 Stat. 1077","children":[],"tail":"; Proc. No. 2695, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1946-07-04"},"text":"July 4, 1946","children":[],"tail":", 11 F.R. 7517, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/1352"},"text":"60 Stat. 1352","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1955-06-30/ch258/s2/a/3"},"text":"June 30, 1955, ch. 258, § 2(a)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/69/242"},"text":"69 Stat. 242","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/271/tIII/s301/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–271, title III, § 301(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-06-02"},"text":"June 2, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/288"},"text":"84 Stat. 288","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/570/tIII/s3111"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–570, title III, § 3111","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-27"},"text":"Oct. 27, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3207-80"},"text":"100 Stat. 3207–80","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/182/tVI/s634"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–182, title VI, § 634","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-12-08"},"text":"Dec. 8, 1993","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/107/2198"},"text":"107 Stat. 2198","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/295"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–295","children":[],"tail":", §§ 3(a)(6)(A), 18(a), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-10-11"},"text":"Oct. 11, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/3515"},"text":"110 Stat. 3515","children":[],"tail":", 3524; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/7/dJ/tI/s127/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–7, div. J, title I, § 127(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2003-02-20"},"text":"Feb. 20, 2003","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/117/441"},"text":"117 Stat. 441","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/429/tI/s1561/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–429, title I, § 1561(a)","children":[],"tail":", (c), title II, § 2106, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-12-03"},"text":"Dec. 3, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/2581"},"text":"118 Stat. 2581","children":[],"tail":", 2582, 2598; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/125/tVIII/s802/d/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–125, title VIII, § 802(d)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-02-24"},"text":"Feb. 24, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/210"},"text":"130 Stat. 210","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id05334512-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id05334513-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id05334514-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Controlled Substances Import and Export Act, referred to in subsec. (m)(2), is title III of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/513"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–513","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-10-27"},"text":"Oct. 27, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/1285"},"text":"84 Stat. 1285","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to subchapter II (§ 951 et seq.) of chapter 13 of Title 21, Food and Drugs. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t21/s951"},"text":"section 951 of Title 21","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id05334515-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section is based on the designated subsections of section 401 of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1930-06-17"},"text":"June 17, 1930","children":[],"tail":", as amended. The last undesignated paragraph of section 401, as added by section 201 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1935-08-05"},"text":"Aug. 5, 1935","children":[],"tail":", was classified to "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1432a"},"text":"section 1432a of this title","children":[],"tail":", prior to being repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/182/s690/c/5"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–182, § 690(c)(5)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-12-08"},"text":"Dec. 8, 1993","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/107/2223"},"text":"107 Stat. 2223","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Words “the Philippine Islands” formerly set out in subsec. (h) were omitted on authority of Proc. No. 2695, which is set out as a note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s1394"},"text":"section 1394 of Title 22","children":[],"tail":", Foreign Relations and Intercourse, and in which the President proclaimed the independence of the Philippines."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"id05334516-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Provisions similar to those in this section were contained in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1922-09-21/ch356/tIV/s401"},"text":"act Sept. 21, 1922, ch. 356, title IV, § 401","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/948"},"text":"42 Stat. 948","children":[],"tail":", which superseded R.S. §§ 2766 and Section 401 of the 1922 act was superseded by section 401 of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1930-06-17"},"text":"June 17, 1930","children":[],"tail":", comprising this section, and repealed by section 651(a)(1) of the 1930 Act."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section III of the Underwood Tariff ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1913-10-03/ch16"},"text":"Act of Oct. 3, 1913, ch. 16","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/38/181"},"text":"38 Stat. 181","children":[],"tail":", amending the Customs Administrative "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1890-06-10/ch407"},"text":"Act of June 10, 1890, ch. 407","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/26/131"},"text":"26 Stat. 131","children":[],"tail":", was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1922-09-21/ch356/s643"},"text":"section 643 of the act of Sept. 21, 1922, ch. 356","children":[],"tail":", title IV, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/989"},"text":"42 Stat. 989","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section III, by subdivision A thereof, amended the Customs Administrative ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1890-06-10/ch407"},"text":"Act of June 10, 1890, ch. 407","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/26/131"},"text":"26 Stat. 131","children":[],"tail":", as previously amended, to read as set forth in section III, subdivisions B–CC. By that amendment and reenactment, the Customs Administrative Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1890-06-10"},"text":"June 10, 1890","children":[],"tail":", and the amendments thereof by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1897-07-24/ch11/s32"},"text":"act July 24, 1897, ch. 11, § 32","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/30/211"},"text":"30 Stat. 211","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1898-05-17/ch341"},"text":"act May 17, 1898, ch. 341","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/30/417"},"text":"30 Stat. 417","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1902-12-15/ch1"},"text":"Act Dec. 15, 1902, ch. 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/32/753"},"text":"32 Stat. 753","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1908-05-27/ch205"},"text":"act May 27, 1908, ch. 205","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/35/403"},"text":"35 Stat. 403","children":[],"tail":", and the Payne-Aldrich Tariff "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1909-08-05/ch6/s28"},"text":"Act of Aug. 5, 1909, ch. 6, § 28","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/36/91"},"text":"36 Stat. 91","children":[],"tail":", were superseded, except the provisions thereof mentioned in a proviso of section IV, S, of that act."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Customs Administrative Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1890-06-10"},"text":"June 10, 1890","children":[],"tail":", as originally enacted and as amended previous to the Payne-Aldrich Tariff Act, consisted of thirty sections, of which section 30 prescribed the time when the act should go into effect. Of the preceding twenty-nine sections of the original act, section 15 providing for review by the courts of decisions of the Board of General Appraisers, was omitted from the act as further amended by the Payne-Aldrich Tariff Act, and the remaining twenty-eight sections were amended thereby, constituting sections 1–28 thereof. A new section, designated as section 29, was added by the Payne-Aldrich Tariff Act, which created a Court of Customs Appeals and prescribed its jurisdiction and powers, proceedings, etc. Its provisions were incorporated in and superseded by chapter 8 of the Judicial Code of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1911-03-03"},"text":"March 3, 1911","children":[],"tail":". Another new section, designated as section 30, was also added by the Payne-Aldrich Tariff Act, which provided for the appointment of an Assistant Attorney-General, a Deputy Assistant Attorney-General, and attorneys, in charge of matters of reappraisement, etc., of imported goods and litigation incident thereto. Section 30 was incorporated into the Code as section 296 of former Title 5, Executive Departments and Government Officers and Employees, and subsequently repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/554"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–554","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1966-09-06"},"text":"Sept. 6, 1966","children":[],"tail":", § 8(a), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/80/632"},"text":"80 Stat. 632","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id05334517-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2004—Subsec. (i). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/429/s1561/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–429, § 1561(c)","children":[],"tail":", repealed "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/7/s127/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–7, § 127(b)","children":[],"tail":". See 2003 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/429/s1561/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–429, § 1561(a)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “, including foreign law enforcement officers,” after “or other person”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (t). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/429/s2106"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–429, § 2106","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (t)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2003—Subsec. (i). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/7/s127/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–7, § 127(b)","children":[],"tail":", which directed amendment of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1401/i"},"text":"section 1401(i) of title 19","children":[],"tail":" by inserting “, including foreign law enforcement officers,” after “or other person”, was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/429/s1561/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–429, § 1561(c)","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (s). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/295/s18/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–295, § 18(a)","children":[],"tail":", amended first sentence generally. Prior to amendment, first sentence read as follows: “The term ‘reconciliation’ means an electronic process, initiated at the request of an importer, under which the elements of an entry, other than those elements related to the admissibility of the merchandise, that are undetermined at the time of entry summary are provided to the Customs Service at a later time.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/295/s3/a/6/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–295, § 3(a)(6)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “recordkeeping,” after “reliquidation,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1993—Subsec. (k). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/182/s634/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–182, § 634(1)","children":[],"tail":", amended subsec. (k) generally. Prior to amendment, subsec. (k) read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) The term ‘hovering vessel’ means any vessel which is found or kept off the coast of the United States within or without the customs waters, if, from the history, conduct, character, or location of the vessel, it is reasonable to believe that such vessel is being used or may be used to introduce or promote or facilitate the introduction or attempted introduction of merchandise into the United States in violation of the laws respecting the revenue.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) For the purposes of sections 1432, 1433, 1434, 1448, 1585, and 1586 of this title, any vessel which—","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(A) has visited any hovering vessel;","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(B) has received merchandise while in the customs waters beyond the territorial sea; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(C) has received merchandise while on the high seas;","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"shall be deemed to arrive or have arrived, as the case may be, from a foreign port or place.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (n) to (s). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/182/s634/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–182, § 634(2)","children":[],"tail":", added subsecs. (n) to (s)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/570/s3111/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–570, § 3111(1)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “, and monetary instruments as defined in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s5312"},"text":"section 5312 of title 31","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (k). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/570/s3111/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–570, § 3111(2)","children":[],"tail":", (3), designated existing provisions as par. (1) and added par. (2)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (m). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/570/s3111/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–570, § 3111(4)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (m)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1970—Subsec. (h). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/271/s301/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–271, § 301(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), struck out subsec. (h) which defined “collector”, and redesignated subsec. (k) as (h)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (i). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/271/s301/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–271, § 301(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), struck out subsec. (i) which defined “comptroller of customs”, redesignated subsec. ("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":") as (i), and, as so redesignated, defined “customs officer”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (j). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/271/s301/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–271, § 301(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), struck out subsec. (j) which defined “appraiser”, and redesignated subsec. (m) as (j)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (k). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/271/s301/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–271, § 301(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (2), redesignated subsec. (n) as (k). Former subsec. (k) redesignated (h)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (","children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"). "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/271/s301/c/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–271, § 301(c)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (3), added subsec. ("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"). Former subsec. ("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":") redesignated (i)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (m), (n). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/271/s301/c/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–271, § 301(c)(2)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated subsecs. (m) and (n) as (j) and (k), respectively."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1955—Subsec. (k). Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1955-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 1955","children":[],"tail":", inserted “Johnston Island”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1938—Subsec. (k). Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1938-06-25"},"text":"June 25, 1938","children":[],"tail":", inserted “Wake Island, Midway Islands, Kingman Reef” before “and the island of Guam”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1935—Subsecs. (","children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":") to (n). Act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1935-08-05"},"text":"Aug. 5, 1935","children":[],"tail":", added subsecs. ("},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":") to (n)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id05334518-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"changeOfName","id":"id05334519-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Change of Name","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“Commissioner of U.S. Customs and Border Protection” substituted for “Commissioner of Customs” in subsec. (p) on authority of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/125/s802/d/2"},"text":"section 802(d)(2) of Pub. L. 114–125","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s211"},"text":"section 211 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":", Domestic Security."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id0533451a-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2004 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/429/tI/s1561/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–429, title I, § 1561(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-12-03"},"text":"Dec. 3, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/2582"},"text":"118 Stat. 2582","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/108/429/tI/s1561/d"},"text":"“This section [amending this section and ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1629"},"text":"section 1629 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and repealing provisions set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1629"},"text":"section 1629 of this title","children":[],"tail":"], and the amendments made by this section, take effect on the date of the enactment of this Act ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-12-03"},"text":"Dec. 3, 2004","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/429/tII/s2108"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–429, title II, § 2108","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-12-03"},"text":"Dec. 3, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/2598"},"text":"118 Stat. 2598","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/108/429/tII/s2108"},"text":"“The amendments made by this subtitle [subtitle B (§§ 2101–2108) of title II of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/429"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–429","children":[],"tail":", amending this section and sections 1484, 1501, 1504, 1514, 1515, and 1520 of this title] shall apply to merchandise entered, or withdrawn from warehouse for consumption, on or after the 15th day after the date of the enactment of this Act ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-12-03"},"text":"Dec. 3, 2004","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id0533451b-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1996 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/295/s3/a/6/A"},"text":"section 3(a)(6)(A) of Pub. L. 104–295","children":[],"tail":" applicable as of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-12-08"},"text":"Dec. 8, 1993","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/295/s3/b"},"text":"section 3(b) of Pub. L. 104–295","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1321"},"text":"section 1321 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id0533451c-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1970 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For effective date of amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/271"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–271","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/271/s203"},"text":"section 203 of Pub. L. 91–271","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1500"},"text":"section 1500 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id0533451d-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1955 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1955-06-30/ch258/s2/d"},"text":"Act June 30, 1955, ch. 258, § 2(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/69/242"},"text":"69 Stat. 242","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/act/1955-06-30/ch258/s2/d"},"text":"“The amendments made by this section [amending this section, sections 1557, 1562, and 1709 of this title, and sections 542, 544, and 545 of Title 18, Crimes and Criminal Procedure] shall take effect on the day following the day on which this Act is enacted [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1955-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1955","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id0533451e-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1938 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1938-06-25/ch679/s37"},"text":"Act June 25, 1938, ch. 679, § 37","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/1094"},"text":"52 Stat. 1094","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/act/1938-06-25/ch679/s37"},"text":"“Sections 31 and 34 of this Act [amending ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1001"},"text":"section 1001 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] shall take effect on the date of enactment of this Act ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1938-06-25"},"text":"June 25, 1938","children":[],"tail":"]. Except as otherwise specially provided in this Act, the remainder of this Act [amending this section and sections 1001, 1201, 1304, 1308, 1309, 1315, 1317, 1402, 1451, 1459, 1460, 1484, 1485, 1491, 1499, 1501, 1516, 1520, 1524, 1553, 1557, 1558, 1559, 1562, 1563, 1603, 1607, 1609, 1613, 1623, and 1709 of this title, enacting sections 1321, 1467, and 1528 of this title, and amending section 331 of former Title 46, Shipping] shall take effect on the thirtieth day following the date of its enactment.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"id0533451f-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of functions, personnel, assets, and liabilities of the United States Customs Service of the Department of the Treasury, including functions of the Secretary of the Treasury relating thereto, to the Secretary of Homeland Security, and for treatment of related references, see sections 203(1), 551(d), 552(d), and 557 of Title 6, Domestic Security, and the Department of Homeland Security Reorganization Plan of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-25"},"text":"November 25, 2002","children":[],"tail":", as modified, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s542"},"text":"section 542 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":". For establishment of U.S. Customs and Border Protection in the Department of Homeland Security, treated as if included in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/296"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–296","children":[],"tail":" as of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-25"},"text":"Nov. 25, 2002","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s211"},"text":"section 211 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":", as amended generally by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/125"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–125","children":[],"tail":", and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/125/s802/b"},"text":"section 802(b) of Pub. L. 114–125","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s211"},"text":"section 211 of Title 6","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of authorities, functions, personnel, and assets of the Coast Guard, including the authorities and functions of the Secretary of Transportation relating thereto, to the Department of Homeland Security, and for treatment of related references, see sections 468(b), 551(d), 552(d), and 557 of Title 6, Domestic Security, and the Department of Homeland Security Reorganization Plan of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-25"},"text":"November 25, 2002","children":[],"tail":", as modified, set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t6/s542"},"text":